tralegislature.org.in/pdf/councilM2014.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315001300/http://maharashtralegislature.org.in/pdf/councilM2014.pdf |archive-date=2016-03-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| 11\n| '''Vacant'''\n|\n|\n| 2014 June\n| 2020 June\n|-\n| 12\n| '''Vacant'''\n|\n|\n| 2014 June\n| 2020 June\n\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Government of Maharashtra]]\n* [[Maharashtra Legislative Assembly]]\n* [[Vidhan Parishad]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Legislatures of India}}\n\n{{coord missing|Maharashtra}}\n\n[[Category:Maharashtra Legislative Council]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox legislature\n| name               = Maharashtra Legislative Council\n| native_name        = \n| coa_pic            = Seal of Maharashtra.png\n| coa_res            = \n| house_type         = Upper house\n| term_limits        = 6 years\n| leader1_type       = Chairman\n| leader1            = [[Ramraje Naik Nimbalkar]]\n| party1             = [[Nationalist Congress Party|NCP]]\n| election1          = 8 July 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/nimbalkar-re-elected-as-maharashtra-council-chairman-116070800379_1.html|title=Nimbalkar re-elected as Maharashtra Council Chairman|date=8 July 2016|accessdate=17 July 2018|publisher=[[Business Standard]]}}</ref>\n| leader2_type       = Deputy Chairman\n| leader2            = [[Neelam Gorhe]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abpmajha.abplive.in/mumbai/shivsena-mla-neelam-gorhe-elected-as-deputy-speaker-of-legislative-council-676422 | title = \u0928\u0940\u0932\u092e \u0917\u094b\u0931\u094d\u0939\u0947 \u092f\u093e\u0902\u091a\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0927\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0930\u093f\u0937\u0926 \u0909\u092a\u0938\u092d\u093e\u092a\u0924\u0940\u092a\u0926\u0940 \u092c\u093f\u0928\u0935\u093f\u0930\u094b\u0927 \u0928\u093f\u0935\u0921 | work = abpmajha.abplive.in}}</ref>\n| party2             = [[Shiv Sena]]\n| election2          = 24 June 2019\n| leader3_type       = Leader of the House\n| leader3            = [[Subhash Desai]]\n| party3             = [[Shiv Sena]]\n| election3          =  16 December 2019\n| leader4_type       = Leader of the Opposition\n| leader4            = [[Pravin Darekar]]\n| party4             = [[BJP]]\n| election4          = 16 December 2019\n| structure1         = Maharashtra_Legislative_Council,_Nov_2019.svg\n| structure1_res     = 300px\n| members            = '''78''' (66 Elected + 12 Nominated)\n| political_groups1  = \n\n'''[[Government of Maharashtra|Government]] (46)'''\n'''[[Maha Vikas Aghadi|MVA]]-[[United Progressive Alliance|UPA]] (46)'''\n* {{Color box|#00B2B2|border=darkgray}} [[Nationalist Congress Party|NCP]] (15)\n* {{Color box|#00BFFF|border=darkgray}} [[Indian National Congress|INC]] (13)\n* {{Color box|#FF6634|border=darkgray}} [[Shiv Sena|SS]] (13)\n* {{Color box|#BC0000|border=darkgray}} [[Peasants and Workers Party of India|PWP]] (1)\n* {{Color box|#999900|border=darkgray}} [[Peoples Republican Party|PRP]] (1)\n* {{Color box|#000000|border=darkgray}} [[Kapil Patil (Lok Bharati) | Lok Bharati]] (1)\n* {{Color box|#A2A2A2|border=darkgray}} [[Independent politician|Independent]] (2)\n\n'''[[Official Opposition (India)|Opposition]] (27)'''\n\n'''[[National Democratic Alliance|NDA]] (27)'''\n* {{Color box|#FF9933|border=darkgray}} [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] (22)\n* {{Color box|#FFFF00|border=darkgray}} [[Rashtriya Samaj Paksha|RSP]] (1)\n* {{Color box|#A2A2A2|border=darkgray}} [[Independent politician|Independent]] (4)\n\n'''Others (5)'''\n* {{Color box|#FFFFFF|border=darkgray}} Vacant (5)\n<br>\n\n| last_election1     = \n| session_room       = Vidhan bhavan mumbai2.JPG\n| meeting_place      = Vidhan Bhavan, Maharashtra Legislative Council, [[Mumbai]], [[India]]\n| website            = http://www.maharashtra.gov.in <br> http://www.mls.org.in\n}}\n\nThe '''Maharashtra Vidhan Parishad''' or '''Maharashtra Legislative Council''' is the upper house of the [[bicameral]] legislature of [[Maharashtra]] [[states and territories of India|state]] in western [[India]].\n\n==Location==\nThe seat of the Vidhan Parishad is situated at the [[Nariman Point]] area of [[South Mumbai]] in the capital [[Mumbai]]. The budget session and the [[monsoon]] session are convened in Mumbai whereas the winter session is convened in the auxiliary capital [[Nagpur]].\n\n==Composition of Legislative Council==\nLegislative Council shall consist of not less than 40 members or maximum one-third of the total number of members in the legislative assembly, chosen in the manner provided in this section.\n\n# 30 members shall be elected by the members of the Legislative Assembly\n# 7 members are elected from amongst graduates from seven divisions of Maharashtra ( Mumbai, Amravati Division, Nashik Division, Aurangabad Division, Konkan Division, Nagpur Division and Pune Division)\n# 7 members are elected from amongst teachers from seven divisions of Maharashtra ( Mumbai, Amravati Division, Nashik Division, Aurangabad Division, Konkan Division, Nagpur Division and Pune Division)\n# 22 members are elected from amongst the local bodies of Maharashtra from 21 divisions of Maharashtra ( Mumbai (2 seats) and one seat each from Ahmednagar, Akola-cum-Washim-cum-Buldhana, Amravati, Aurangabad-cum-Jalna, Bhandara- Gondiya, Dhule-cum-Nandurbar, Jalgaon, Kolhapur, Mumbai, Nagpur, Nanded, Nashik, Osmanabad-cum-Latur-cum-Beed, Parbhani-Hingoli, Pune, Raigad-cum-Ratnagiri-cum-Sindhudurg, Sangli-cum-Satara, Solapur, Thane-cum-Palghar, Wardha-cum-Chandrapur-cum-Gadhchiroli and Yavatmal)\n# 12 members having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of matters such as literature, science, art, co-operative movement and social serviceshall be nominated by the Governor\n\nIt is a continuous House and not subject to dissolution. However, one-third of its members retire every second year and are replaced by new members. As such a member enjoys a tenure of six years. The members of the Vidhan Parishad elect its chairman and deputy chairman.\n\n===Current Composition of Legislative Council===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Party !! Members\n|-\n| [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] || 22\n|-\n| [[Nationalist Congress Party]] || 15\n|-\n| [[Indian National Congress]] || 13\n|-\n| [[Shiv Sena]] || 13\n|-\n| [[Independent politician|Independents]] || 06\n|-\n| [[Rashtriya Samaj Paksha]] || 01\n|-\n| [[Peasants and Workers Party]] || 01\n|-\n| [[Peoples Republican Party]] || 01\n|-\n| [[Kapil Patil (Lok Bharati) | Lok Bharati]] || 01\n|-\n| Vacant || 05\n|-\n! '''Total''' !! '''78'''\n|}\n\n==Constituencies and Members==\n''See here, [[List of members of the Maharashtra Legislative Council]]''.\n\n'''Keys:'''\n{{legend2|#FF9933|[[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] (22) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#00B2B2|[[Nationalist Congress Party|NCP]] (15) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#00BFFF|[[Indian National Congress|INC]] (13) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#E3882D|[[Shiv Sena|SHS]] (13) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#DDDDDD|[[Independent politician|Independent]] (6) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|grey|[[Rashtriya Samaj Paksha|RSP]] (1) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#BC0000|[[Peasants and Workers Party of India|PWP]] (1) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#999900|[[Peoples Republican Party|PRP]] (1) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#003366|[[Kapil Patil (Lok Bharati) | Lok Bharati]] (1) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFFF|Vacant (5) |border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n\n===Elected by Vidhan Sabha Members (30)===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! #\n! Member\n! colspan=\"2\"| Party\n! Date of Appointment\n! Date of Retirement\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Anil Parab]]\n| bgcolor=#E3882D|\n| [[Shiv Sena]]\n| 2018 July\n| 2024 July\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Manisha Kayande]]\n| bgcolor=#E3882D|\n| [[Shiv Sena]]\n| 2018 July\n| 2024 July\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Babajani Durani]]\n| bgcolor=#00B2B2|\n| [[Nationalist Congress Party]]\n|