und-elected-unopposed-on-the-maharashtra-legislative-council/articleshow/73329276.cms | title = \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0935\u093f\u0915\u093e\u0938 \u0906\u0918\u093e\u0921\u0940\u091a\u0947 \u0938\u0902\u091c\u092f \u0926\u094c\u0902\u0921 \u0935\u093f\u0927\u093e\u0928 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u0937\u0926\u0947\u0935\u0930 \u092c\u093f\u0928\u0935\u093f\u0930\u094b\u0927  | work = maharashtratimes.indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n| bgcolor=#00B2B2|\n| [[Nationalist Congress Party]]\n| 2020 Jan\n| 2022 Jul\n|-\n| 22\n| [[Neelam Gorhe]]\n| bgcolor=#E3882D|\n| [[Shiv Sena]]\n| 2014 Apr\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 23\n| Anand Thakur\n| bgcolor=#00B2B2|\n| [[Nationalist Congress Party]]\n| 2014 Apr\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 24\n| Kiran Pawaskar\n| bgcolor=#00B2B2|\n| [[Nationalist Congress Party]]\n| 2014 Apr\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 25\n| Hemant Takle\n| bgcolor=#00B2B2|\n| [[Nationalist Congress Party]]\n| 2014 Apr\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 26\n| Harisingh Rathod\n| bgcolor=#00BFFF|\n| [[Indian National Congress]]\n| 2014 Apr\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 27\n| Arun Adsad<ref>https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/bjp-s-adsad-elected-unopposed-to-maharashtra-legislative-council-1348323-2018-09-25</ref>\n| bgcolor=#FF9933|\n| [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| 2018 Oct\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 28\n| [[Smita Wagh]]\n| bgcolor=#FF9933|\n| [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| 2015 Jan\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 29\n| Prithviraj Deshmukh\n| bgcolor=#FF9933|\n| [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| 2019 June\n| 2020 Apr\n|-\n| 30\n| '''Vacant'''\n| \n|\n|\n| 2020 Apr\n\n|}\n\n===Local Authorities' constituencies (22)===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! #\n! Constituency\n! Member\n! colspan=\"2\"| Party\n! Date of Appointment\n! Date of Retirement\n|-\n| 1\n| '''Mumbai (1)'''\n| [[Ramdas Kadam]]\n| bgcolor=#E3882D| \n| [[Shiv Sena]]\n|  2016\n| 2022<ref name=\"dna.india\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/report_Congress-Sena-bag-council-seats-in-mumbai-BJP-man-loses_1325912|title=Congress, Sena bag Council seats in Mumbai; BJP man loses|publish